**CASTING CALL ‚Äî FEATURE FILM ‚Äî VANCOUVER**

**PAID BUT FORGOTTEN**
Independent Psychological Thriller / Drama

Casting principal roles for an upcoming feature film currently in development.

**PROJECT**

A once-celebrated writer living in isolation becomes convinced his life is being shaped by forces beyond his control. As coincidences and fractured memories collapse past and present into a single unsettling design, others are drawn into a story that may be writing them too.

**Visual tone:** Modern black-and-white cinematography with selective color accents.
Character-driven, cinematic, psychologically grounded.

**ROLES**

**RHONDA**
Female, 35‚Äì50
Black actors strongly encouraged to submit. Trans women welcome.
A high-profile investigative journalist ‚Äî sharp, charismatic, relentless ‚Äî whose professional curiosity becomes personal entanglement.

**Feature shoot:** approx. 1‚Äì2 days

**LEROY**
Male, 35‚Äì50
Indigenous / First Nations actors strongly encouraged to submit.
A community leader rebuilding his life while helping others do the same ‚Äî grounded, soulful, quietly powerful.

**Feature shoot:** approx. 3 days

**PREVIEW SHOOT (Proof-of-Concept)**

Actors cast will carry forward into the feature.

A short **non-union, unpaid preview shoot** will capture approximately **15 seconds of finished footage per role** for a **45-second funding trailer** supporting post-production grant applications.

**Preview shoot timeframe:** ASAP ‚Äì January to early February 2026
**Time commitment:** approx. 1‚Äì2 hours per actor

**FEATURE PRODUCTION**

**Principal photography:** February 2026 ‚Äî Vancouver
**Feature compensation:** $225/day for principal roles

Shooting days scheduled efficiently and flexibly to accommodate availability.

**AUDITION PROCESS**

Selected actors will receive sides and a self-tape request.
Shortlisted performers may be invited for a brief virtual or in-person callback.
Grounded, natural performances preferred.

**SUBMISSIONS**

Please send:

‚Ä¢ Headshot
‚Ä¢ Resume
‚Ä¢ Demo reel or performance link (if available)

**Submit to:** casting@horstcreative.ca
**Submission deadline:** January 23, 2026

Writer / Director: Jared Horst
Production: Horst Creative
horstcreative.ca

üé¨ Final Countdown for FilmPlatforms.com ‚Äì Join as a Founding Member
Hi everyone,

After months of focused work, FilmPlatforms.com is entering its final testing phase.

We are building a global industry community designed for the entire film ecosystem ‚Äî from early-career professionals to established industry experts, production companies, and studios.

Our goal is to bring the film industry together on one modern, intuitive platform, covering real professional needs:

‚úÖ Industry Profiles

Create individual or company profiles to present your work, experience, and services.

‚úÖ Professional Status System

Members identify as Early-Career Professionals or Industry Professionals, helping create transparent, meaningful industry discussions.

‚úÖ Jobs & Collaboration

International job opportunities, collaborations, and casting-related conversations.

‚úÖ Festivals, Marketing & Industry Insight

Discussions and tools around festivals, promotion, distribution, and industry trends.

üîç Beta Test ‚Äì Limited Access

Before our official launch in a few days, I‚Äôm inviting 20‚Äì30 film industry professionals to participate in a short 2-day beta test.

The goal is to validate:

visual experience

usability and user journey (UX)

clarity of the professional structure

üéÅ Why join as a beta tester?

‚ú® Founding Member Status

Your personal or company profile will remain active after the official launch.

‚ú® Direct Influence

Your feedback will directly shape the final version of FilmPlatforms.

‚ú® Personal Thank You

I will personally reach out to every tester to thank them for contributing.

If you‚Äôd like to take part and get early access before the public launch,

comment ‚ÄúInterested‚Äù, and I‚Äôll send you the details via DM.

Thank you for helping us build something meaningful for the film industry üé•

items.text:
CREW SEARCH - LOS ANGELES - LATE FEB 2026 - INDIE PILOT 

The basics: Director looking for LA local crew to fill multiple positions for an independent series! Production dates are February 19-28, but you would not necessarily need to work all shoots.

The production: Angel Reincarnate is a sci-fi drama series with a surrealist take on very real questions. Beginning with one grieving young woman's entry into a study aiming to prove reincarnation and unraveling into something much murkier, Angela's journey explores what we do for money, meaning and answers to life's mysteries.

The positions: 
* Camera operator 
* Gaffer 
* Audio mixer
* Boom operator
* PA

Compensation: This will be discussed based on position, involvement and a rate you are comfortable with.

If interested in any position in this project, please email mar@angelreincarnate.info and leave a comment to let me know!

items.text:
AUDITIONS OPEN: Collection of Short Plays in March in London

Happy New Year! We‚Äôre Broadmai Productions, and we‚Äôre excited to announce that auditions are now open for our upcoming performance, HAYWIRE: The Dark Side of New Technology. The performances will be held at The Drayton Arms on 22nd & 23rd March 2026, starting at 7:30 PM each night. (Cast required all day on 22nd March for get-in and from 18:00 each night). 

Auditions will be online and open tomorrow, 13th January, and continue until 24th January. All ages, genders and levels of experience welcome. If you‚Äôre interested in auditioning, please email us at: contact@broadmai-productions.co.uk

Please express interest by 23rd January.

Once you reach out, we‚Äôll send you the scripts for the four short plays: PostMax6000, Wonderful, Beyond the Grave, and Simon. 

_______

AUDITION DETAILS:

 ‚Ä¢ Auditions are 20-minute slots. You will be asked to audition with 2-3 pages of your choice from the provided scripts.

 ‚Ä¢ Ideally, be off book, but it‚Äôs fine if not. 

 ‚Ä¢ The characters are flexible in terms of gender and age, except those for Beyond the Grave, which requires two male actors who resemble father and son.

_______

PLAY DESCRIPTIONS:

 ‚Ä¢ PostMax 6000: The PostMax 6000 is invented! A vast underground postal system capable of delivering

hundreds of letters across the country per second! But what‚Äôs this?! It‚Äôs just sucked Kinkelbert George inside! Will he be delivered to freedom? Or lost in postal purgatory?

 ‚Ä¢ Wonderful: Ben signs up for a research programme for a new-age medical device. It can detect hereditary

illness and diseases that he could develop‚Ä¶but it also lets him know, and hear, exactly how his

ancestors died. As detections become increasingly intense, Ben learns that knowledge about death is better left untold ‚Äî especially when it comes to children.

 ‚Ä¢ Beyond the Grave: A mysterious phone is delivered. When it rings, Reece answers it and finds his deceased father on the other end. Overwhelmed to hear his voice again and to learn that there is a way to bring him back to life, Reece starts to wonder if the rules of death are better left unbroken‚Ä¶

 ‚Ä¢ Simon: Simon has an all-inclusive getaway booked and paid for by his work. The location is perfect, the

hotel is perfect, Simon is perfect. And so is Simon ‚Äî the other Simon. And the other Simon. Wait, how many Simons are there?! Who‚Äôs the real Simon?!

_______

REHEARSALS: 

 ‚Ä¢ Rehearsals will be in-person in London, with a commitment of 1-2 sessions per week until the performances.

_______

COMPENSATION:

 ‚Ä¢ This will be a profit-share arrangement, with profits distributed after expenses are covered.

items.text:
Hello everyone. 
After taking a nearly 2 year break from acting I've decided I want to get into it again but feel completely lost. I am 17 years old and have been in independent films along with stage productions. How should I go about getting back into it? 
Thank you

topComments.text: Get hold of a copy of the Actors and Performers Yearbook, which will give you a solid overview into how the UK industry functions. A library should have a copy, or could order one for you to borrow, or you might find a copy second-hand on ebay. The best way to build the foundation for a successful long-term career is to go to one of the top drama schools and train intensely for three years. There's no argument, statistically, against that. However, there are an increasing number of part-time schools, shorter courses and online training options. Most of the drama schools tend to prefer students with a little more life experience, though getting in at 18 years old can happen. In the meantime, take some classes, keep working in the theatre, keep doing student films. There are a few casting platforms you can join once you're 18: sites like Mandy, Backstage or Casting Callback. It's not too hard to pick up bits and pieces of work as an actor: character work in theme parks, unpaid films, student projects, profit-share theatre etc. However, paying the bills with acting work is another matter, and would need you to reach a very good level in terms of your skills, discipline, work ethic and ability to deal with the ups and downs of the industry.

Training & get an agent.
The FB page recommended on here for your parents to join has loads of helpful info including recommended agents.

sharedPost.text:
Casting : "Maybe its love, maybe not"

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone
I am always open and honest. You can earn no money on this. but maybe there is a good film in the end promoting for you.
I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch
Thats me 
www.imdb.com/name/nm1591928
Get in touch under Thomas.Goersch@vodafonemail.de 
please ask for details.

Trailer mit intensiver spanischer Stimmung suche ich einen ausdrucksstarken Mann, der Lust hat, ein besonderes Projekt mit zum Leben zu erwecken.

Wen ich suche:
‚Ä¢ Du hast einen s√ºdeurop√§ischen / mediterranen Look.
‚Ä¢ Du kannst dich sehr gut bewegen zu Latin Musik und hast ein gutes K√∂rpergef√ºhl.          ‚Ä¢hast Lust auf ein kreatives Projekt mit viel Leidenschaft und Rhythmus.
Zum Projekt:

Wir drehen einen Tanz-PoC , den wir bei internationalen Festivals einreichen werden. Das Ziel ist es, aus diesem POC ein gro√üeres Filmprojekt zu entwickeln. Das ist eine super Chance f√ºr deine Sichtbarkeit.

Da es ein No-Budget-Herzensprojekt ist, gibt es keine Gage, aber:
Wir √ºbernehmen deine Reisekosten.
Es gibt volle Verpflegung am Set.
Sichtbarkeit bei Festivals.

Hast du Lust auf spanische Vibes und eine tolle Zusammenarbeit? Dann schreib mir gerne eine Nachricht mit Foto oder einem kurzen Video √ºber mediterran-film@web.de .

Ich freue mich auf dich !

AUDITIONS OPEN: Collection of Short Plays in March in London

Happy New Year! We‚Äôre Broadmai Productions, and we‚Äôre excited to announce that auditions are now open for our upcoming performance, HAYWIRE: The Dark Side of New Technology. The performances will be held at The Drayton Arms on 22nd & 23rd March 2026, starting at 7:30 PM each night. (Cast required all day on 22nd March for get-in and from 18:00 each night). 

Auditions will be online and open tomorrow, 13th January, and continue until 24th January. All ages, genders and levels of experience welcome. If you‚Äôre interested in auditioning, please email us at: contact@broadmai-productions.co.uk

Please express interest by 23rd January.

Once you reach out, we‚Äôll send you the scripts for the four short plays: PostMax6000, Wonderful, Beyond the Grave, and Simon. 

_______

AUDITION DETAILS:

 ‚Ä¢ Auditions are 20-minute slots. You will be asked to audition with 2-3 pages of your choice from the provided scripts.

 ‚Ä¢ Ideally, be off book, but it‚Äôs fine if not. 

 ‚Ä¢ The characters are flexible in terms of gender and age, except those for Beyond the Grave, which requires two male actors who resemble father and son.

_______

PLAY DESCRIPTIONS:

 ‚Ä¢ PostMax 6000: The PostMax 6000 is invented! A vast underground postal system capable of delivering

hundreds of letters across the country per second! But what‚Äôs this?! It‚Äôs just sucked Kinkelbert George inside! Will he be delivered to freedom? Or lost in postal purgatory?

 ‚Ä¢ Wonderful: Ben signs up for a research programme for a new-age medical device. It can detect hereditary

illness and diseases that he could develop‚Ä¶but it also lets him know, and hear, exactly how his

ancestors died. As detections become increasingly intense, Ben learns that knowledge about death is better left untold ‚Äî especially when it comes to children.

 ‚Ä¢ Beyond the Grave: A mysterious phone is delivered. When it rings, Reece answers it and finds his deceased father on the other end. Overwhelmed to hear his voice again and to learn that there is a way to bring him back to life, Reece starts to wonder if the rules of death are better left unbroken‚Ä¶

 ‚Ä¢ Simon: Simon has an all-inclusive getaway booked and paid for by his work. The location is perfect, the

hotel is perfect, Simon is perfect. And so is Simon ‚Äî the other Simon. And the other Simon. Wait, how many Simons are there?! Who‚Äôs the real Simon?!

_______

REHEARSALS: 

 ‚Ä¢ Rehearsals will be in-person in London, with a commitment of 1-2 sessions per week until the performances.

_______

COMPENSATION:

 ‚Ä¢ This will be a profit-share arrangement, with profits distributed after expenses are covered.

items.text:
Filmmakers!. Unleash your creativity and join a vibrant community of passionate filmmakers who are dedicated to bringing stories to life! Together, we'll craft captivating narrative films, forge valuable connections, and fuel our artistic visions. 

This is more than just filmmaking; it's a journey to elevate our craft and careers to new heights! Every Saturday from 4-6 PM near DTLA, we gather to share ideas, collaborate, and inspire one another. If you're truly committed to making an impact in the world of film and ready to embark on this exciting adventure, we invite you to become a part of our filmmaking family. Membership is completely free! 

Complete this form to join us. https://forms.gle/bb58i1Hc5rzzg2ju7

Hello all,

I‚Äôm a filmmaker from Markham, Ontario directing a feature film funded by Telefelim Canada‚Äôs Talent-To-Watch program. Searching for my  TWO leads, both of Filipino background. If you think you know anyone that would be interested please share.

Info below!

CANADA-WIDE CASTING CALL (Non-Union) // AWAY WITH DAD // FEATURE FILM

Paid Opportunity
Filming Location: Renfrew County, Ontario
Tentative dates: Mid August - End of September 2026

Set in Algonquin Park, Away With Dad is a candid story of a father and his adult son who make the drastic decision of going on a backpacking trip in the wilderness with no running water or electricty in order to focus on creating a stronger bond between them.

Casting for the following Lead Roles:
Thomas - Male, Filipino, 45 - 65 years old, speaks Visayan or Tagalog
TJ - Male, Filipino, 20 - 35 years old

NO ACTING EXPERIENCE REQUIRED. Camping experience an asset. Must be a Canadian Citizen. 

Director: Kyle Credo Producer: Farah Abdo 
If interested please email office@awdfilm.com a photo of yourself and a video (2 minutes MAX) stating your full name, what languages you can speak. For the remainder of the video please tell us about yourself: your upbringing, where you grew up and your hobbies, likes, dislikes, etc. Anything that helps us get to know you better!" us get to know you better!"

AUDITIONS OPEN: Collection of Short Plays in March in London

Happy New Year! We‚Äôre Broadmai Productions, and we‚Äôre excited to announce that auditions are now open for our upcoming performance, HAYWIRE: The Dark Side of New Technology. The performances will be held at The Drayton Arms on 22nd & 23rd March 2026, starting at 7:30 PM each night. (Cast required all day on 22nd March for get-in and from 18:00 each night). 

Auditions will be online and open tomorrow, 13th January, and continue until 24th January. All ages, genders and levels of experience welcome. If you‚Äôre interested in auditioning, please email us at: contact@broadmai-productions.co.uk

Please express interest by 23rd January.

Once you reach out, we‚Äôll send you the scripts for the four short plays: PostMax6000, Wonderful, Beyond the Grave, and Simon. 

_______

AUDITION DETAILS:

 ‚Ä¢ Auditions are 20-minute slots. You will be asked to audition with 2-3 pages of your choice from the provided scripts.

 ‚Ä¢ Ideally, be off book, but it‚Äôs fine if not. 

 ‚Ä¢ The characters are flexible in terms of gender and age, except those for Beyond the Grave, which requires two male actors who resemble father and son.

_______

PLAY DESCRIPTIONS:

 ‚Ä¢ PostMax 6000: The PostMax 6000 is invented! A vast underground postal system capable of delivering

hundreds of letters across the country per second! But what‚Äôs this?! It‚Äôs just sucked Kinkelbert George inside! Will he be delivered to freedom? Or lost in postal purgatory?

 ‚Ä¢ Wonderful: Ben signs up for a research programme for a new-age medical device. It can detect hereditary

illness and diseases that he could develop‚Ä¶but it also lets him know, and hear, exactly how his

ancestors died. As detections become increasingly intense, Ben learns that knowledge about death is better left untold ‚Äî especially when it comes to children.

 ‚Ä¢ Beyond the Grave: A mysterious phone is delivered. When it rings, Reece answers it and finds his deceased father on the other end. Overwhelmed to hear his voice again and to learn that there is a way to bring him back to life, Reece starts to wonder if the rules of death are better left unbroken‚Ä¶

 ‚Ä¢ Simon: Simon has an all-inclusive getaway booked and paid for by his work. The location is perfect, the

hotel is perfect, Simon is perfect. And so is Simon ‚Äî the other Simon. And the other Simon. Wait, how many Simons are there?! Who‚Äôs the real Simon?!

_______

REHEARSALS: 

 ‚Ä¢ Rehearsals will be in-person in London, with a commitment of 1-2 sessions per week until the performances.

_______

COMPENSATION:

 ‚Ä¢ This will be a profit-share arrangement, with profits distributed after expenses are covered.

I am Thomas Goersch from Stuttgart Germany. 
Actor and Filmdirector. 
I am making Independent Movies.
I present my movies on International Film festivals and was lucky to receive some awards. 
But the work is not about awards and money, its about making movies for the people to think about.
My next movie is a modern love story:
An elderly man is meeting another younger, very attractive man in the Internet.  But they are from different Continents. They start a long distance relastionship ship. which is full of passion and desire. 
One day the younger man starts to ask for money, cause he is a Student and no more able to pay his bills. 
The older man is full of distrust.
Is he only there  to pay his lovers bills or is there love between them ?
A story with two endings.
One with true love and one with betrayl.
I am looking for the young attraktive Lover.
Men  25 to 42 years old,  good looking  who is able to film his parts on his own by smartshone

I guess its not necessary that an educated actor is playing this part. so feel free to get in touch

please ask for details.

**CASTING CALL - "Her Eyes Only"**

Filming in Brighton | Filming March 9th - 16th | Roles Paid 

Hello Everyone!! We are students from BIMM MetFilm Brighton and are currently casting for our upcoming Grad Short Film "Her Eyes Only"!! 

We are looking for to collaborate with passionate and reliable performers!! Ideally looking for Brighton locals or those willing to travel !!

**STORYLINE**

‚ÄúHer Eyes Only‚Äù follows the story of Vera Galea with an unusual side hustle: blackmail. By day she‚Äôs invisible, by night she becomes an anonymous vigilante using her unique skills to expose predators on behalf of the people they‚Äôve wronged. Disguising herself on each of her ‚Äòdates‚Äô, she escapes from her own past ‚Äì a humiliating betrayal by her ex-boyfriend that destroyed her life. But when a target recognizes her from that very scandal, Vera‚Äôs carefully constructed world begins to unravel. Forced to confront the trauma that fuels her cause, she spirals between empowerment and self-destruction, blurring the line between justice and obsession.

**ROLES**

Vera Galea (Early 20s) - a deeply morally grey woman. Ruthless and desperate for revenge. She is effortlessly magnetic, calculated and sharp. She plays an intimidating role as she switches through disguises on each given date but also feels the pain of her past and she finds herself in the cyle of blakcmail and fear.

James (Early 20s) - a typical rugby lad, leaning towards arrogant.

Jack (Early 20s) - Vera‚Äôs ex boyfriend, desperate for

her back, persistent but slimey.

Mickey (Early 20s) - a slim, tattoed, painfully vain type.

Vera's Dates (Early 20s) - ideally looking for three individuals of various male sterortypes

To Apply: Send your Headshot, CV or Spolight (if available), and availability to hannahmohammedhd@gmail.com

items.text:
Heimatbewusstsein: Ist Patriotismus heute n√∂tig, oder schon gef√§hrlich? 

Du bekommst in 90 Sekunden eine klare Perspektive auf Zugeh√∂rigkeit, Identit√§t und innere Heimat. 

Pfarrer Nils Petrat parkt sein gelbes Checker Taxi in K√∂ln und stellt uns eine Frage, die in einer globalisierten, oft un√ºbersichtlichen Welt pl√∂tzlich wieder √ºberall auftaucht: Was bedeutet Heimatbewusstsein heute, und wie stehst Du zu Patriotismus, Nationalstolz und diesem sp√ºrbaren Heimattrend? 

In dieser Folge sind Sandra und ich, Christian, als exklusive Interviewpartner dabei. Ich formuliere es bewusst so, wie es viele Menschen f√ºhlen, aber selten sauber aussprechen: 

In einem gesunden Ma√ü, ohne Gewalt, ohne Hass, ohne √úberh√∂hung, kann Nationalstolz und Patriotismus etwas sein, das Halt gibt. F√ºr mich geh√∂rt das Wissen, woher man kommt, zu den Grundbed√ºrfnissen des Menschen. Es geht um Zugeh√∂rigkeit, und genau deshalb spielen Menschen, Gruppen, Orte, kulturelle G√ºter, religi√∂se Werke und Feste eine zentrale Rolle. Das kann etwas Kostbares sein, etwas, das man sichtbar pflegt, nicht als Kampfansage, sondern als Ausdruck von Wertsch√§tzung. 

Spannend wird es dort, wo Heimat nicht nur als Ort verstanden wird, sondern als innerer Zustand. Als Christ hat Heimat f√ºr mich vor allem eine innere Dimension: ein seelisches Zuhause, ein innerer Hafen. Und genau hier entsteht der eigentliche Konflikt unserer Zeit, denn viele Debatten behandeln Heimat wie ein reines Au√üen, Flagge, Symbol, Folklore. Dabei geht es im Kern um Bindung, Sinn, Sicherheit, Gemeinschaft und Identit√§t. 

Wenn man das √ºbersieht, versteht man auch nicht, warum Menschen so emotional reagieren, wenn das Thema Heimat in Schlagzeilen, Talkshows oder Social Media auftaucht.

Heimatbewusstsein: Ist Patriotismus heute n√∂tig, oder schon gef√§hrlich? 

Du bekommst in 90 Sekunden eine klare Perspektive auf Zugeh√∂rigkeit, Identit√§t und innere Heimat. 

Pfarrer Nils Petrat parkt sein gelbes Checker Taxi in K√∂ln und stellt uns eine Frage, die in einer globalisierten, oft un√ºbersichtlichen Welt pl√∂tzlich wieder √ºberall auftaucht: Was bedeutet Heimatbewusstsein heute, und wie stehst Du zu Patriotismus, Nationalstolz und diesem sp√ºrbaren Heimattrend? 

In dieser Folge sind Sandra und ich, Christian, als exklusive Interviewpartner dabei. Ich formuliere es bewusst so, wie es viele Menschen f√ºhlen, aber selten sauber aussprechen: 

In einem gesunden Ma√ü, ohne Gewalt, ohne Hass, ohne √úberh√∂hung, kann Nationalstolz und Patriotismus etwas sein, das Halt gibt. F√ºr mich geh√∂rt das Wissen, woher man kommt, zu den Grundbed√ºrfnissen des Menschen. Es geht um Zugeh√∂rigkeit, und genau deshalb spielen Menschen, Gruppen, Orte, kulturelle G√ºter, religi√∂se Werke und Feste eine zentrale Rolle. Das kann etwas Kostbares sein, etwas, das man sichtbar pflegt, nicht als Kampfansage, sondern als Ausdruck von Wertsch√§tzung. 

Spannend wird es dort, wo Heimat nicht nur als Ort verstanden wird, sondern als innerer Zustand. Als Christ hat Heimat f√ºr mich vor allem eine innere Dimension: ein seelisches Zuhause, ein innerer Hafen. Und genau hier entsteht der eigentliche Konflikt unserer Zeit, denn viele Debatten behandeln Heimat wie ein reines Au√üen, Flagge, Symbol, Folklore. Dabei geht es im Kern um Bindung, Sinn, Sicherheit, Gemeinschaft und Identit√§t. 

Wenn man das √ºbersieht, versteht man auch nicht, warum Menschen so emotional reagieren, wenn das Thema Heimat in Schlagzeilen, Talkshows oder Social Media auftaucht.

I'm new to the page. I was a Broadway and Broadway touring actor for 20 years. I'm now a headshot photographer here in the city. 

I'm doing this cool new thing(It's free) to help actors make mindful choices when posting headshots to Backstage and Actors Access. 

The goal is more auditions that you are right for.   

It should be fun and enlightening. Have to join by Monday the 12th to take part. 

Bonus: Everyone that takes part will get a free headshot review and someone will win a free headshot session(4 look).

items.text:
Hi fellow actors,

My name is Ibbi and I‚Äôm an actress who graduated from Mountview, and wrote, produced and played in my own short film, HYSTERIA.

I started writing my short, while living in London, and I didn‚Äôt have any writing experience what so ever.

HYSTERIA  is a dramatic short, which highlights inequality in the healthcare system, where gender bias and structural racism still prevail.
Please give HYSTERIA a warm welcome ‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è
I hope I can inspire some of you! Remember, you don‚Äôt have to be a pro to make things happenüí™üèæüî•

**üé¨ CASTING CALL: *****Illusions of Grandeur ***

******Live Action******

*A Short Film by *Jordan Jackson

**Genre: Drama / Coming-of-Age**

**Tone: Gritty realism with a child‚Äôs imaginative lens**

**COMPENSATION: Unpaid :( , Lunch, Copy of Footage **

**Filming Dates: End of January or Early February **

***Please Submit by January 20th, 2025 :)**

**[EMAIL jjacks24@uccs.edu FOR SIDES]**

**LOCATION: Colorado Springs **

**Logline:**

A young boy‚Äôs love for his superhero idol blurs with reality when he discovers his hero ‚Äî and his father ‚Äî isn‚Äôt the savior he imagined.

**üß¢ JOEY (6‚Äì12)**
**Description:** Innocent, imaginative, and full of heart. Joey escapes his unstable home through superhero fantasies. He believes good always wins ‚Äî even when the world around him says otherwise.
**Type:** Young actor capable of conveying wonder, playfulness, and heartbreak.

**üåπ ELISE (16‚Äì20)**
**Description:** Joey‚Äôs older sister and reluctant guardian. She‚Äôs grown up too fast ‚Äî sharp, tired, protective. She carries both resentment and love for her family‚Äôs situation.
**Tone:** Grounded realism, emotional restraint with underlying warmth.

**üïØÔ∏è JOEY‚ÄôS MOM (Late 20s‚Äì30s)**
**Description:** Overworked and emotionally exhausted. Trying to hold her family together while fighting her own quiet collapse. Her phone calls reveal more than she ever tells her children.
**Type:** Actor who can express fatigue, vulnerability, and quiet strength.

**ü•Ä GENTLEMAN PERFECT / JAMES (30s‚Äì40s)**
**Description:** Once a man of pride and potential ‚Äî now homeless, addicted, and haunted by his past. In Joey‚Äôs eyes, he‚Äôs a superhero; in reality, he‚Äôs a fallen one. A tragic, layered role requiring depth, subtlety, and broken charisma.
**Tone:** Complex mix of dignity, shame, and fading hope.

**üóùÔ∏è HOMELESS MAN (40s‚Äì50s)**
**Description:** A street survivor who represents the darker side of desperation. Not evil, but lost. Brief appearance, but a pivotal moment showing Joey‚Äôs innocence colliding with danger.

**üíî YOUNG MAN / MUGGER (18‚Äì22)**
**Description:** A mirror of what Joey could become ‚Äî young, broke, trying to survive. His confrontation with Gentleman Perfect reveals both the world‚Äôs cruelty and the man‚Äôs lingering morality.

**üíÑ WOMAN (20s‚Äì30s)**
**Description:** Victim of the mugging; small role but emotionally grounding. Her scene reinforces Joey‚Äôs belief that Gentleman Perfect is still a hero ‚Äî just before that belief unravels.

**üë¨ ERIC (18‚Äì22)**
**Description:** Joey‚Äôs friend ten years later. Provides contrast and realism ‚Äî he wasn‚Äôt there to see the ‚Äúheroics.‚Äù Grounded, observant, a reminder that nostalgia and truth rarely match.

**üåá OLDER JOEY (Late teens‚Äì20s)**
**Description:** Once full of imagination, now hardened by betrayal. Still searching for something heroic in a world that let him down. His closing narration brings the story full circle.

**üìÖ Production Notes**
* **Setting:** Urban neighborhood; mostly night exteriors.
* **Tone:** Visual realism with moments of childhood wonder.
* **Themes:** Hero worship, family, addiction, disillusionment, legacy.
* **Shooting Length:** 10‚Äì12 pages (~10‚Äì15 minutes).

CASTING CALL - Unpaid Independent Short Film.

TITLE: Ringer

**Production Type:** Independent Short Film

**Location:** Arvada, Northglenn, Colorado.

**Compensation:** Unpaid

**Union Status:** Non-Union

**Filming Window:** End of March

LOGLINE: A Manic pixie Dream Girl type plot goes south when the characters become aware that they're in a movie.

GENRE: Horror

ROLES:

CRAIG - (Male, 20s): A very down to earth and relatable guy, who has a special interest in music, but is also somewhat shy at times and will hesitate before speaking up for himself.

DECEMBER - (Female, 20s): A quirky manic pixie dream girl, who loves filmmaking, especially really old films from the 30s - 50s, and appears very happy and bubbly, but holds a darker side when she begins to questions the things around her.

SOPHIE - (Female, 20s): A punk rock tomboy who appears tough on the surface, but has a soft side underneath. While she has suffered through past trauma, she doesn‚Äôt stop it from letting her care about any of her friends.

NOTE: We are especially looking for actors who can do great improv and can play the character, and a fictionalized version of themselves. 

TO SUBMIT: Please email at alecopedia@gmail.com with a message saying you are interested and the subject line, ‚ÄúRinger Audition - [INSERT ACTOR NAME]‚Äù. From there you will be given a link to a folder, where you may submit your Headshot, Resume, and Reel, along with an Audition Side of each character you want to audition for.

DEADLINE: Friday, January 16th

üé¨ CASTING CALL ‚Äì HORROR feature film üé¨
Hey everyone,
I‚Äôm currently looking for actors for an independent horror project titled:
FLYING TO MADNESS
This is a psychological horror film inspired by travel vlogs, haunted locations, and reality-bending horror. With a lot of twists
üëª ABOUT THE PROJECT
3 sisters travel to Ibiza for a girls holiday.
After taking drugs and exploring a remote location, they become trapped in a looping nightmare involving a haunted house that won‚Äôt let them leave.
Think:
Psychological horror
Creeping dread rather than cheap jump scares
This is a low-budget indie project, made for experience, showreels, and festival submissions.
üé≠ ROLES AVAILABLE

ACTORESS 1
Female, early‚Äìmid 20s
Slim built or curvy 
Confident, outgoing, ‚Äúleader‚Äù type
Comfortable acting on camera and improvising dialogue
Lots of screen time available 

ACTORESS 2
Female, early‚Äìmid 20s
Slim built or curvy
More cautious / sarcastic personality
Strong reactions and emotional range
Lots of screen time available 

ACTORESS 3 
Female early - mid 20s
Slim built
Shy/Inclosed soft voice
Good with emotional expressions
Lots of screen time available 

ACTOR 4
Male, any age 20s‚Äì40s about 6 foot plus. 
Slim built
Mysterious, unsettling presence
Minimal dialogue but strong physical acting
Horror-focused role
No previous acting experience required ‚Äî just commitment and reliability.

üìç LOCATION
Filming location: (UK-based project)
Scotland four days in September 
Southend beach for one hour any time available 
Hotel scenes is for half a day but can do during scotland trip
London basement for two hours in October 
Nightclub scene for two hours in April the 22nd at 6pm as location I‚Äôd already booked
And an hour at a studio for greenscreen Footage. Anytime available 
Passport might be needed for actor 1 and 2 as we need a scene on a plane or might be able to edit in with greenscreen effect
Mostly interior scenes
Small cast, long shoot schedule
üí∞ PAYMENT
Unpaid / at the time of filming
10% rotary payments after the film sells. 
but travel expenses covered as can be picked up by the director from your location you want. And taking to the filming location. And Brought home after the scenes
If your making your own way to the scenes we can‚Äôt cover travelling 
Food provided on shoot days
Full credit given
Will help to spice up your portfolio and get more experience as main actors in the film.
üì© HOW TO APPLY
If interested, please message our private company WhatsApp on 07492853834 
Or if you want you can email on mpl.87@outlook.com 

with:
Your name
Age
Any acting experience (if any)
A recent photo or selfie
Availability
also send a short intro video.
If you love horror, indie films, or want experience working on a creative project, I‚Äôd love to hear from you.
Thanks!
‚Äî Matt Littlechild 
Writer / Director ‚Äì Flying to Madness

items.text:
üé• Looking for Confident On-Camera Talent for Public Interaction TikTok Videos 

I‚Äôm looking for a confident, charismatic on-camera personality for a series of short-form, public-interaction videos for a wellness brand.

This role is heavily improv-based. You‚Äôll be approaching people in public and engaging in real, unscripted conversations on camera. The ability to think on your feet, read people quickly, and go back-and-forth naturally is essential.

This is not scripted acting. The content is playful, high-energy, conversational, and humor-driven ‚Äî not aggressive or mean-spirited.

You do not need to film or edit anything. I will handle all production. You just need to be comfortable on camera and talking to strangers.

$20/hour 

Please send any similar content you‚Äôve done or even your Instagram/tiktok link helps.

topComments.text:
Hello! 

I would be perfect for this.

I‚Äôm a naturally charismatic and outgoing person who thrives on connecting with others. I‚Äôve dabbled in comedy and commercial acting, which has given me strong improv skills and the confidence to think on my feet in unscripted situations. I‚Äôm also very comfortable on camera, having performed regularly as a singer on my church‚Äôs worship team, which has taught me how to engage an audience and be authentic in front of people.

I genuinely enjoy playful, high-energy interactions and have a knack for reading people quickly and responding naturally ‚Äî exactly what‚Äôs needed for spontaneous public engagement content. I‚Äôm confident I can bring fun, relatable energy to your TikTok videos while making people feel at ease on camera.

I‚Äôm interested, but have no context.

When? Where? For how long? 

What will I be asked to talk about or react? 

I‚Äôm a great improviser, but won‚Äôt step in front of a camera without more security/context.

Actors!. Unleash your creativity and join a vibrant community of passionate filmmakers who are dedicated to bringing stories to life! Together, we'll craft captivating narrative films, forge valuable connections, and fuel our artistic visions. 

This is more than just filmmaking; it's a journey to elevate our craft and careers to new heights! Every Saturday from 4-6 PM near DTLA, we gather to share ideas, collaborate, and inspire one another. If you're truly committed to making an impact in the world of film and ready to embark on this exciting adventure, we invite you to become a part of our filmmaking family. Membership is completely free! 

Complete this form to join us. [https://forms.gle/bb58i1Hc5rzzg2ju7](https://forms.gle/bb58i1Hc5rzzg2ju7?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExOWgxMkV1M0hERHZPcnRiZHNydGMGYXBwX2lkEDIyMjAzOTE3ODgyMDA4OTIAAR5k9IvyEVLNR7KSIH-49als_mHzt2jmGaMVG-0US9AEEf0j7Noco2gsk8uinQ_aem_Bhp-OAZ6lp-AUQSLYq-m5Q)

sharedPost.text:
Watching Your Friends And Fellow Artists
¬†
‚ÄúActing requires a creative and compassionate attitude.¬† It must aim to lift life up to a higher level of meaning and not tear it down or demean it.¬† The actor‚Äôs search is a generous quest for that larger meaning.¬† 
¬†
‚ÄúThat‚Äôs why acting is never to be done passively.¬† When I watch some of you I sense you‚Äôre not really involved.¬† Some of you become totally detached from the work of other students in the class.¬† There‚Äôs an unspoken criticalness or indifference, which 
is disruptive to the class and hinders you from learning.¬† It‚Äôs a trait that ill serves actors.¬† Instead of being critical and judgmental, we should recognize and honour others‚Äô efforts.¬† Criticizing others, and belittling others only diminishes us.¬† And if our goal is always size, that‚Äôs heading in the wrong direction!‚Äù
- Stella Adler, The Art of Acting 
¬†
¬† ‚ÄúAnother word of counsel about watching the creative work of others.¬† Begin to exercise your sense of truth by looking, first of all, for the good points.¬† In studying another‚Äôs work, limit yourself to the role of a mirror and say honestly whether or not 
you believe in what you have seen and heard and point out particularly the moments 
that were most convincing to you.‚Äù
¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬†¬† -¬†Tortsov, An Actor Prepares, by Constantin Stanislavsky

items.text:
‚ú® FREE LIVE STREAMED NEW PLAY READING THIS THURSDAY 

January 15, 2026 | 8:00 PM

Join us for a FREE public reading of Aurora, a new one-woman show written and performed by Amy Abrigo.

About the Show:

Aurora is a deeply personal work inspired by Amy‚Äôs grandmother and her journey with Alzheimer‚Äôs. Through memory, storytelling, and love, the play explores the stories we carry ‚Äî and what happens when they begin to slip away.

Run Time: 2 hours including a 15min intermission.

üìç Location:

Black Potion 

1900 Fredericksburg Rd, Suite 101

San Antonio, TX 78201

üöó FREE PARKING available in the lot behind Panader√≠a Jim√©nez, as well as street and neighborhood parking.

üëê Accessibility:

This event will be ASL interpreted by Bebe Amaro from Stage Hands LLC., making the reading accessible to Deaf and hard-of-hearing audience members.

üíú Wear Purple for Alzheimer‚Äôs Awareness üíú

We invite you to wear purple, the color of Alzheimer‚Äôs awareness, as we gather for Aurora.

üôå Community Partners üôå 

The Alzheimer‚Äôs Association and the Alzheimer‚Äôs Division of Meals on Wheels San Antonio will be attending the event and hosting resource tables in the lobby. Please plan to arrive early to meet their representatives, ask questions, and explore the resources available to our community.

üéÇ Birthday Treats for a Cause üç™

We‚Äôll be offering birthday cake and cookies, with donations gladly accepted via cash, Cash App, PayPal, or Venmo.

üéüÔ∏è Admission is FREE, and while tickets are free, donations are welcome and appreciated to support this meaningful work.

We hope you‚Äôll join us for an evening of storytelling, community, and awareness.

About the Date:

This reading takes place on January 15, 2026 ‚Äî Aurora‚Äôs birthday, 90 years to the day after she was born. It is both a celebration of her life and a reflection on memory, legacy, and the people who shape us.

From the Playwright: 

‚ÄúThis story is about my grandmother ‚Äî but it‚Äôs also about memory, and all the stories we hold inside us that are erased when we are gone. The play is called Aurora, named for her. We will be reading it on her birthday. I hope you will join us.‚Äù

‚Äî Amy Abrigo

üç∫ About the Venue:

Black Potion is San Antonio‚Äôs original tabletop game tavern, serving craft and local beer, wine, and food ‚Äî plus games, puzzles, gifts, and more. Come early to shop, play, dine, drink, and settle in before the reading begins.

üé• Can‚Äôt attend in person?

The event will be live-streamed. The link will be posted in this Facebook event ‚Äî please RSVP to receive updates: https://www.facebook.com/share/1EqduDUctT/

üôè Special Thanks:

This project is supported in part by the City of San Antonio Department of Arts & Culture through an FY25 Individual Artist Grant.

We hope you‚Äôll join us for this intimate evening of storytelling and remembrance.

*DIGITAL ART OPEN-CALL OPPORTUNITY IN NYC*

Start the new year by exhibiting your work **on Madison Ave** in NYC. This one-night digital art show at a five-level speakeasy art studio inside Herbwell, seeks artworks exploring **rebirth, evolution, endings, beginnings, and transformation**. Showcase your art in the same neighborhood as monumental museums and galleries like the MoMa.

All digital mediums welcome: Digital Paintings & Illustration, 3D Modeling & Digital Sculpture, Digital Collage & Vector Art, Digital Photography, Pixel Art, GIF Art / Animation, Glitch Art, Generative Art, Augmented Reality (AR) Art, Virtual Reality (VR) Art, AI Art, Mixed Media (with digital components), Video Art & Motion Graphics, NFTs & Blockchain-Backed Works, Interactive & Installation-Based Digital Works, Derivative works (where you hold rights to exhibit), Scanned Physical Works

**Why submit?**

‚Ä¢ Showcase your work in one of NYC‚Äôs most prestigious art corridors
‚Ä¢ Photos, documentation, and press coverage included
‚Ä¢ Connect with curators, collectors, and international artists
‚Ä¢ Feature in a multi-disciplinary event blending digital art, traditional art, and live music

If your work speaks to stepping into something new ‚Äî we‚Äôd love to see it.

**Apply here:** [https://hug.art/open-calls/New-Year-Exhibition-on-Madison-Ave-in-NYC](https://hug.art/open-calls/New-Year-Exhibition-on-Madison-Ave-in-NYC)
